      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and knead",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the flour, yeast, salt, sugar, and cardamom. Add the warm milk and soft butter and bring together to a dough. Knead for 10 minutes by hand or 6 minutes in a stand mixer with a dough hook, until smooth and elastic. The dough will be soft but not sticky.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bulk ferment, about 60 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place the dough in an oiled bowl, cover with a damp cloth, and leave until doubled. About 60 minutes in a warm kitchen.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, fill, and shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the filling ingredients to a smooth paste. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough to a rectangle about 40×50 cm. Spread the filling evenly to within 1 cm of the edges. Fold the dough in thirds lengthwise to make a long strip about 13 cm wide, pressing the layers gently together. Cut crosswise into 16 strips of about 2.5 cm each. For the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "knotted bun shaping",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "knotted bun shaping",
                  "termId": "cmpbjxg0o0000ikv45qkf27jr"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", wrap each strip once around two fingers, then thread the tail through the loop and tuck it under the base. Alternatively, simply coil each strip into a round on the tray for the simpler version.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prove, glaze, and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Arrange the buns on lined baking trays with 5 cm between each. Cover loosely and leave for 30 minutes until slightly puffed. Preheat the oven to 220°C conventional. Brush each bun with beaten egg and scatter with pearl sugar. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until deep gold on the peaks and set in the centre. They should feel light and spring back to a gentle press. Cool on a rack; they are best eaten warm, within an hour of baking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
